Executive Profile
Roger J. Maggs  Founder and Partner, Celtic House Venture Partners Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 13 different industries.See Board Relationships71--
Background

		Mr. Roger J. Maggs is the Founder and Partner at Celtic House Venture Partners Inc. Mr. Maggs founded Celtic House in 1994. He oversees Celtic House’s investment activities in the United Kingdom and Ireland. Having mentored over a dozen Chief Executive Officers in Celtic House’s portfolio, he has skills in the area of management team development. Before Celtic House, he had over 27 years of experience in senior management and venture activities at Alcan Aluminum Limited. ... He started at Alcan Aluminum as a Physicist in a product development lab. Mr. Maggs held several senior positions including the Vice President of Mergers, Acquisitions and Divestments in the President at Alcan Metal Marketing where he was responsible for marketing of Alcan's primary metal sales worldwide, recycling operations in North America and raw materials supply; the Vice President of Personnel; the Chief Executive Officer at Alcan Aluninio del Uruguay; the Vice President at Latin American Regional Headquarters of Alcan; and the President at Alcan Corporate Ventures. He served as the President of Alcan Global Metal Marketing and Recycling. Over his career, he has held Directorships on over 30 public and private Boards. Through his longstanding board role at LTX-Credence, he has built strong ties to the semiconductor industry. He serves as the Chairman of Port Talbot Waterfront Enterprise Zone and Port Talbot Seafront Enterprise Zone. He has been the Non-Executive Chairman and Independent Director of Sandvine Corporation since March 7, 2006. He has been Independent Director of Spectra7 Microsystems Inc. since February 5, 2013 and Xcerra Corporation since June 1994. Mr. Maggs serves on the Boards of Spectra7 Microsystems (Ireland) Limited, noHold, Inc. He has been an Independent Director at Spectra7 Microsystems Inc., since February 5, 2013. He served as the Chairman of the Board at Spectra7 Microsystems Inc. since November 14, 2015 until December 7, 2015. He served as Lead Director of Xcerra Corporation. He served on the Boards of Movidius Ltd, Global Silicon Ltd., Third Brigade, Inc., Bridgewater Systems Corporation, Rio Tinto Alcan, Inc., BlazePhotonics Ltd, BlueArc Corporation, Oclaro, Inc., CrossKeys, nCipher Limited, Orchestream Canada Corporation, Spar Aerospace Limited, Synad Technologies, TimeStep Corp., and Ubiquity Software Corporation Limited. He served as a Director of Cavendish Kinetics, Inc. He is an Honorary Fellow of the University of Wales, Swansea and a Governor of Clifton College. Mr. Maggs holds a Physics degree from the University of Wales and a Master's degree from Warwick Business School.Read Full Background




