Insider Activity


Individual




Roger J. Maggs



Prior to co-founding Celtic House in 1994, Mr. Maggs enjoyed a 27-year career with Alcan Aluminum Limited, a global metals company. Mr. Maggs has held senior positions at Celtic House since 1994. He was President and Chief Executive Officer of Alcan Aluminum Limited from 1986 to 1994. He currently sits on the boards of Cavendish Kinetics, RedMere Technology, Sandvine (IPO on LSE-AIM and TSX), and LTX Corporation (NASDAQ: LTXX).
Mr. Maggs has also served on the boards of Blazephotonics (acquired by Crystal Fibre), BlueArc, Bookham Technology, CrossKeys, nCipher, Orchestream , SPAR Aerospace (1990-1994), Synad Technologies (acquired by STMicroelectronics), TimeStep (acquired by Newbridge Networks) and Ubiquity Software (acquired by Avaya).
Mr. Maggs received a degree in Physics from the University of Wales and a Master's degree from Warwick Business School.



